article.description: — Zach Freemantle had 17 points and 10 rebounds as Xavier topped Butler 63-51 on Sunday night.
article.headline: Freemantle leads Xavier past Butler 63-51
article.story: CINCINNATI -- — Zach Freemantle had 17 points and 10 rebounds as Xavier topped Butler 63-51 on Sunday night. Colby Jones added 13 points and 11 rebounds for the Musketeers. Jason Carter had 10 points for Xavier (12-4, 5-4 Big East Conference). Paul Scruggs added six assists. Butler totaled 20 points in the second half, a season low for the team. Chuck Harris had 14 points, eight rebounds and six assists for the Bulldogs (7-13, 6-11). Jair Bolden added 12 points. Bryce Golden had 10 points and 12 rebounds. The Musketeers improve to 2-0 against the Bulldogs on the season. Xavier defeated Butler 68-55 on Jan. 30. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
